'''Stuart Smith''' is a New Zealand politician who was elected to the New Zealand parliament at the [[New Zealand general election, 2014|2014 general election]] as a representative of the [[New Zealand National Party]].

==Political career==
{{NZ parlbox header}}
{{NZ parlbox
 |term=51st
 |start={{NZ election link year|2014}}
 |end=present
 |list=62
 |party=New Zealand National Party
 |electorate=[[Kaik<U+014D>ura (New Zealand electorate)|Kaik<U+014D>ura]]
}}
{{NZ parlbox footer}}
Smith is a former chairman of the New Zealand Winegrowers Association. In 2013 he contested the [[New Zealand National Party|National Party]] selection for the [[Kaik<U+014D>ura (New Zealand electorate)|Kaik<U+014D>ura]] seat, defeating incumbent [[Colin King]].<ref>[http://www.stuff.co.nz/marlborough-express/news/9530084/Smith-picked-over-King Smith picked over King] ''stuff.co.nz'', 18 December 2013</ref> He was elected at the [[New Zealand general election, 2014|2014 election]] with a preliminary majority of 11,510 votes.<ref>{{cite web |title=Election Results -- Electorate Status |url= http://2005.electionresults.govt.nz/electoratestatus.html |publisher=[[Electoral Commission (New Zealand)|Electoral Commission]] |accessdate=20 September 2014}}</ref>

